The paper proposes a novel program repair scheme that is applicable to production directly, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The experiments conducted involve testing the system on real-world software applications, which could fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR) or systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques for patch generation could also suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
